text.tspan: DALYs from mental health and substance use disorder by age, World
DALYs (Disability-Adjusted Life Years) rate by age, measured per 100,000 individuals. DALYs are used to measure
total burden of disease - both from years of life lost and years lived with a disability. One DALY equals one lost year
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease
